Package: metanorm
Type: Package
Title: Quality Control And Sample-Based Normalization of Metabolomics Data
Version: 0.9.0
Author: Matthijs Vynck
Maintainer: Matthijs Vynck <matthijs.vynck@ugent.be>
Description: metanorm provides implementations of robust Gaussian and scaled-t
    generalized additive models for normalization of metabolomics data. Such
    normalization is typically done using quality control samples, but this
    implementation supports also sample-based normalization, and different
    weightings of quality control and samples can be used. Further, metanorm
    includes vanilla implementations of QC-RLSC, QC-RSC, and a robustified
    implementation of QC-RLSC. Normalization is done on a compound-by-compound
    basis, and parallelized normalization default.
